# Shell & SSR Conventions

## Shell (packages/shell/)

- Entry client: `src/entry-client.tsx` — hydrates with `initialData` from SSR
- Entry server: `src/entry-server.tsx` — `renderToPipeableStream` with streaming
- `ShellApp.tsx` — parses URL `/{accountId}/{slug}/` to determine app
- `MFESlot.tsx` — loads remotes via Module Federation runtime
- `LyxDevtools.tsx` — shared state inspector (dev only)

## URL Parsing

The regex for accountId accepts both MongoDB ObjectIds and custom aliases:
```
/^\/([a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]{1,30}[a-z0-9]|[a-f0-9]{24})\/([^/]+)/
```

## Module Federation

- Each MFE gets a **unique** remote name: `{mfeName}_v{version}` (underscores replace dots)
- This prevents MF runtime cache collisions when the same MFE has different versions in different slots
- `loadRemote` result must be cast: `mf.loadRemote(...) as { default: ComponentType } | null`

## SSR Server (platform/ssr/)

- `server.js` — Express with `/health`, `/_assets/` (static), `/:accountId/:slug` (SSR)
- Reserved paths (`health`, `api`, `storage`, `_assets`, `admin`, etc.) are NOT treated as accountId
- API proxy: `/api/*` → admin-api, `/storage/*` → S3
- Assets use `/_assets/` base path (not `/apps/`)
- Vite configs: `base: "/_assets/"` in both `vite.config.ts` and `vite.ssr.config.ts`
